<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,338,431,457]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Discussion.</emphasis>
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Jin, 1995" authorityName="Jin" authorityYear="1995" box="[676,1294,432,458]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Leptoteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneoensis" subGenus="Rhinoteratura">
<emphasis box="[676,1180,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Leptoteratura (Rhinoteratura) borneoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jin, X. B. &amp; Yamasaki, T." box="[1187,1294,432,458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="81 - 84" refId="ref3221" refString="Jin, X. B. &amp; Yamasaki, T. (1995) Remarks on the genus Leptoteratura Yamasaki, 1982 and a new species from North Borneo (Grylloptera: Tettigonioidea: Meconematidae). Proceedings of Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, No. 53, 81 - 84." type="book chapter" year="1995">Jin, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 1993" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Leptoteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharovi" subGenus="Rhinoteratura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Leptoteratura (Rhinoteratura) sharovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[536,728,472,498]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="87 - 89" refId="ref3014" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1993) A contribution to the knowledge of the tribe Meconematini (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 2 (1), 85, 87 - 89." type="journal article" year="1993">Gorochov, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in: (1) male cerci lamellate, strongly curled; (2) male subgenital plate with slightly concave posterior margin; (3) female subgenital plate inflated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
In addition, according to the original description and diagnostic figures of 
<taxonomicName authority="Yamasaki, 1988" authorityName="Yamasaki" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Leptoteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="symmetrica">
<emphasis box="[1126,1436,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Leptoteratura symmetrica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yamasaki, T." box="[151,347,592,618]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="37 - 42" refId="ref3428" refString="Yamasaki, T. (1988) Two new Meconematine taxa of Genus Leptoteratura (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) from the Ryukyu Islands. Proceedings of Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, No. 38, 37 - 42." type="book chapter" year="1988">Yamasaki, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: cerci symmetrical, anterior margin of fastigium of vertex almost truncate and so on, we transfer it to subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[418,584,632,657]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Leptoteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Rhinoteratura">
<emphasis box="[418,584,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Rhinoteratura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
